=begin
  transmog_inventory.lic

  Inspects every transmogrification (appearance-transfer) item stored in a
  container -- by default a chest in your locker -- and writes a catalog to a
  CSV file listing each item's noun, full name, where it is worn, and quantity.
  The CSV opens directly in Excel and imports cleanly into Google Sheets.

  Usage:
    Scan (MERGES results into the saved list, deduped by full name):
      ;transmog_inventory               scans the default container (nouned "chest")
      ;transmog_inventory backpack      scans a container you name instead of "chest"
      ;transmog_inventory chest debug   dump raw ANALYZE/INSPECT for 2 items

    Fresh scan (WIPES the saved list first, then scans from scratch):
      ;transmog_inventory new           wipe the list, then scan "chest"
      ;transmog_inventory new backpack  wipe the list, then scan a container you name
      ;transmog_inventory fresh|reset|rebuild ...   aliases for new

    Search the saved CSV:
      ;transmog_inventory search neck            any column contains "neck"
      ;transmog_inventory search ring neck       AND: contains "ring" AND "neck"
      ;transmog_inventory search noun:ring       Noun column contains "ring"
      ;transmog_inventory search loc:neck        Worn Location contains "neck"
      ;transmog_inventory search noun:band loc:finger   combine fields
      ;transmog_inventory find ...               alias for search

    Remove an entry (when you use/trade/sell an item):
      ;transmog_inventory remove twisted ora ring     remove the single match
      ;transmog_inventory remove noun:band loc:finger combine fields
      ;transmog_inventory remove all noun:ring        remove every match
      ;transmog_inventory rm|delete|del ...           aliases for remove

      Field prefixes: noun:/n:  name:/full:/f:  loc:/location:/worn:/l:

      ;transmog_inventory help          this help

    Upload your catalog to the Transmog Exchange (shared web database):
      ;transmog_inventory upload        push your saved CSV to the exchange

  How it works:
    - Each candidate item is briefly pulled into your hand so it can be
      ANALYZEd (to confirm it is a transmog) and INSPECTed (to learn where it
      is worn), then it is returned to the container.
    - "Transmog" is confirmed via the ANALYZE line:
      "...transfer its appearance onto another compatible worn item..."
    - Worn location comes from INSPECT ("you could wear the <noun> ..."). Items
      that block INSPECT are recorded with an "unknown" location.
    - Items inside a LOCKER have volatile game IDs that the game re-rolls every
      30-60 seconds. The script therefore tracks items by their full name and
      re-LOOKs in the container to refresh IDs whenever a GET or PUT fails,
      retrying a few times before giving up on an item.
    - Identical (same-named) items are catalogued once with a quantity.

  Requirements:
    - Stand at your OPEN locker with the chest accessible (so "look in chest"
      works), or have the container worn/held on you.
    - At least one free hand.

  Output:
    <lich>/scripts/transmog/transmog_inventory_<character>.csv
    Columns: Noun, Full Name, Worn Location, Quantity

         author: Mara
           game: Gemstone
           tags: transmog, inventory, locker, items
        version: 1.1.1
=end

require 'csv'
require 'net/http'
require 'openssl'
require 'json'
require 'securerandom'

# Changelog:
# 1.3.0 (2026-06-17)
#   - Added "note" command with stable numeric item IDs for easy reference.
#     Each catalog entry is assigned a persistent 9-digit ID (stored in CSV).
#     Primary syntax: ;transmog_inventory note <id> <note text>
#     Fallback:       ;transmog_inventory note <search terms> -- <note text>
#     IDs are shown in search/remove output and survive re-scans via merge.
#   - Notes (max 120 chars) are included in uploads and shown on the website.
#   - Notes and ID columns added to CSV (backward compatible).
#   - QTY column retained in CSV for local tracking but no longer shown on site.
#
# 1.2.0 (2026-06-17)
#   - Added "upload" command: POSTs the local CSV to the Transmog Exchange
#     central database (Supabase). Character names are claimed on first upload
#     via a locally-stored UUID token; only the same machine can overwrite.
#     See https://github.com/Lillymara/transmog-exchange for the web interface.
#
# 1.1.1 (2026-05-31)
#   - Bugfix: each scanned item is now returned in an ensure block so exceptions
#     or interrupted logic do not leave it stranded in hand.
#   - Bugfix: quantity is now persisted to CSV (new "Quantity" column) instead of
#     only being shown in console output.
#   - Backward compatible: older CSV files without "Quantity" are read as qty=1.
#
# 1.1.0 (2026-05-31)
#   - Scans now MERGE results into the saved list by default (deduped by full
#     name), so you can build a catalog across multiple containers.
#   - Added "new" (aliases fresh/reset/rebuild) to wipe the saved list and scan
#     from scratch.
#   - Added "remove" (aliases rm/delete/del) to delete catalog entries using the
#     same search syntax; refuses to remove when more than one entry matches
#     unless prefixed with "all" (guards against accidental mass deletion).
#   - Refactored search/remove onto a shared catalog reader/writer and matcher.
# 1.0.0 (2026-05-31)
#   - Initial release.

# Candidate Lich item types that can ever be a transmog item (mirrors eloot/foreach).
TRANSMOG_TYPES   = /jewelry|clothing|armor|weapon|uncommon/i
TRANSMOG_LINE    = /transfer its appearance onto another compatible worn item/i

# Maps an INSPECT "you could wear ..." phrase onto a canonical worn location
# and its game code (matching INVENTORY USAGE / INVENTORY LOCATION).
# Ordered most-specific first; the first matching regex wins.
#   [regex, canonical location label, location code]
SLOT_MAP = [
  [/slipped into,? on your chest|into,? on your chest|as a gambeson|as an undershirt/i, "Slipped into, on your chest", 23],
  [/over your chest|around your chest|on your chest|covers? the torso|as armor/i,       "Over your chest", 8],
  [/slipped into,? on your legs|as leggings/i,                                          "Slipped into, on your legs", 24],
  [/attached to your legs|attaching it to your legs|as leg greaves/i,                   "Attached to your legs", 15],
  [/pulled over your legs|on your legs|over your legs|as pants|as trousers|as a skirt/i, "Pulled over your legs", 7],
  [/slipped on your feet|on your feet,? as socks|as socks|as stockings/i,               "Slipped on your feet", 21],
  [/on your feet|on a foot|as boots|as shoes|as sandals|as slippers/i,                  "On your feet", 11],
  [/from both ears|from your ears|as a pair of earrings/i,                              "Hung from both ears", 17],
  [/from (?:a |one |your |an )?(?:single )?ear|as a single earring|as an earring/i,     "Hung from a single ear", 16],
  [/around your neck|around the neck|hung around your neck|as a necklace/i,             "Hung around your neck", 12],
  [/draped (?:over|from) your shoulders|hanging it from your shoulders|hanging from your shoulders|over your shoulders|as a cloak/i, "Draped over your shoulders", 6],
  [/slinging it across your shoulders and back|slung (?:over|across) your shoulder|as a shield/i, "Slung over your shoulder", 5],
  [/on your back|as a backpack/i,                                                       "On your back", 2],
  [/attached to your arms|attaching it to your arms|around your arms|as arm greaves|on your arms|over your arms|as armbands?|as bracers?/i, "Attached to your arms", 14],
  [/attached to your wrist|attaching it to your wrist|around your wrist|on your wrist|as a bracelet|as a wristlet/i, "Attached to your wrist", 9],
  [/slipped over your hands|over your hands|on your hands|as gloves/i,                  "Slipped over your hands", 20],
  [/on (?:a|your) fingers?|around your fingers?|onto a finger|as a ring/i,              "On your fingers", 10],
  [/around your waist|as a belt|as a sash/i,                                            "Around your waist", 3],
  [/attached to your belt|attaching it to your belt|as a belt pouch/i,                  "Attached to your belt", 13],
  [/attached to your ankle|attaching it to your ankle|around your ankle|on your ankle|as an anklet/i, "Attached to your ankle", 18],
  [/put over your front|over your front|as an apron/i,                                  "Put over your front", 19],
  [/placed in your hair|in your hair|as a barrette/i,                                   "Placed in your hair", 22],
  [/on (?:top of )?your head|atop your head|over your head|as a (?:hat|helm|crown|circlet)/i, "On your head", 4],
  [/as a pin|pin-worn|on your body/i,                                                   "As a pin", 1],
]

